snippet.textDisplay: An unpopular opinion here... but although I enjoyed both Parasite and The Lighthouse... I thought they were both over-rated in terms of cinematic experience. As someone who watches a lot of foreign film, Parasite didn't surprise me much in terms of character development and storytelling - as many Korean films in the genre execute these types of themes exceptionally well or even better in my experience.  And Lighthouse... I thought the acting was outstanding and the choice in style of cinematography was perfect... but still... I walked away being okay if I never saw it again, nor would it be on my list of "must see" movies.
